      "side": 1,
      "message": "When the device is connected with an external keyboard and Caps Lock key is pressed, the key event will be F16 with a MOD3_DOWN flag. If user set \"Caps Lock -\u003e Control\" keyboard mapping, the rewritten key event will be Control with CAPS_LOCK_ON flag. Then to keep keyboard caps lock state synchronized with key event, InputMethodChromeOS [1] turns caps lock state on.\n\nSo the solution is to remove this CAPS_LOCK_ON flag.\n\n[1] https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/ui/base/ime/input_method_chromeos.cc?q\u003dinput_method_chromeos\u0026dr\u003dC\u0026l\u003d82",
